The REST endpoints for Organizations return NULL

{code}
curl --request GET   --url 'https://api.atlassian.com/admin/v1/orgs'   --header 'Authorization: Bearer <redacted>'   --header 'Accept: application/json'
{code}

Response:
{code}
{"data":[],"links":{"self":"https://api.atlassian.com/admin/v1/orgs"},"meta":null}
{code}

{panel:borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#6A8EB3 |bgColor=#F8F8F8}
(!) This only affect [Organizations|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/organization-administration-938859734.html] with [Multi-authentication policies|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/authentication-policies-1018779823.html]
{panel}

h3. Problem Definition
When the admins enforce _SAML SSO_ (at _Org_ > _Security_ > _Authentication policies_) for any policy (with at least one user added to it) nothing happens when they try to delete the SAML Integration (at _Org_ > _Security_ > _SAML single sign-on_).

Analyzing the browser's request, we can see that the issue happens because SAML is enforced by default:
!image.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Suggested Solutions
Create a message to inform the customers why they can't remove the integration. Here is an example of a message: 
{quote}
You can't delete the SAML configuration because it is enforced as a default authentication policy. Remove it from there before you can proceed. 
{quote}
